[{"id":39048,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Atomic Physics","question":"","options":["$25 \\mathrm{a}_{0}$","$9 a_{0}$","$16 \\mathrm{a}_{0}$","None of the above"],"answer":2,"solution":"Energy of photon $=\\frac{\\mathrm{hc}}{\\lambda}=\\frac{12500}{980}=12.75 \\mathrm{eV}$\r\n\r\nEnergy of electron in $\\mathrm{n}^{\\text {th }}$ orbit is given by\r\n\r\n$\\mathrm{En}=\\frac{-13.6}{\\mathrm{n}^{2}} \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{E}_{\\mathrm{n}}-\\mathrm{E}_{1}=-13.6\\left[\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{n}^{2}} \\frac{-1}{1^{2}}\\right]$\r\n\r\n$\\Rightarrow 12.75=13.6\\left[\\frac{1}{1^{2}} \\frac{-1}{\\mathrm{n}^{2}}\\right] \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{n}=4$\r\n\r\n$\\therefore$ Electron will excite to $\\mathrm{n}=4$ We know that ' $R^{\\prime} \\propto n^{2}$\r\n\r\n$\\therefore$ Radius of atom will be $16 \\mathrm{a}_{0}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39084,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Atomic Physics","question":"","options":["$\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{Ze}}$","$v^2$","$\\frac{1}{m}$","$\\frac{1}{v^4}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\frac{1}{m}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2006","image":null},{"id":39034,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Atomic Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi><mi>c</mi></mrow><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi><mi>c</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>Rhc</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>c</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>c</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#62;</mo><mo>&#62;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8658;</mo></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>c</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8734;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (02 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":38964,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Atomic Physics","question":"","options":["r","$\\sqrt{\\mathrm{r}}$","$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{\\mathrm{r}}}$","$\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{r}}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{F}_{\\mathrm{C}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{mv}^2}{\\mathrm{r}} \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{Kq}_1 \\mathrm{q}_2}{\\mathrm{r}^2}=\\frac{\\mathrm{mv}^2}{\\mathrm{r}} \\\\ & \\mathrm{mv}^2 \\mathrm{r}^2=K \\mathrm{~K}_1 \\mathrm{q}_2 \\mathrm{r} \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{L}^2}{\\mathrm{~m}}=K \\mathrm{Kq}_1 \\mathrm{q}_2 \\mathrm{r} \\\\ & \\mathrm{L} \\propto \\sqrt{\\mathrm{r}}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39073,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Atomic Physics","question":"","options":["$81.0 \\mathrm{eV}$","$135.4 \\mathrm{eV}$","$203.4 \\mathrm{eV}$","$156.6 \\mathrm{eV}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":39025,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Atomic Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi>n</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi></msub><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#8733;</mo><mfrac><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">1</mn><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi></msub><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#8733;</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn mathvari